Computer Sciences Corporation - Wikipedia






















 






Computer Sciences Corporation

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Computer Sciences Corporation





Former type

Public


Traded as
NYSE: CSC


Industry
IT services, IT consulting


Fate
Merged with Hewlett Packard Enterprise Services; formed DXC Technology


Successor
DXC Technology


Founded
April 1959; 58 years ago (1959-04)


Founder
Roy Nutt
Fletcher R. Jones


Defunct
April 3, 2017


Headquarters
Tysons Corner, Virginia, United States



Area served

Worldwide



Key people

John Michael Lawrie, (Chairman, President and CEO)[1]


